1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2063b of Title 63, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 As used in the Oklahoma Community Health Worker Act:
5 1. “Certified community health worker” means a community health
6 worker to whom the State Department of Health has issued a
7 certificate to practice as a certified community health worker in
8 this state;
9 2. “Community health worker” means a frontline health worker
10 who has a shared understanding of and is a trusted member of the
11 community being served; and
12 3. “Department” means the State Department of Health.
13 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2063c of Title 63, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. The State Department of Health shall establish a certificate
17 for community health workers. This certification shall be
18 voluntary.
19 B. A certified community health worker may:
20 1. Serve as a liaison between health and social services and
21 the community to facilitate access to services, to improve the
22 quality of service delivery, and to maximize the efficiency of
23 service delivery by coordinating available resources and leveraging
24 partnerships with private, nonprofit, or faith-based organizations;
SB424 HFLR Page 2
